cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the energy efficiency of heterogeneous networks, which is a topic related to network optimization and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of small cells for data transmission, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
